 "body": "<p>Interest paid by corporate PFI operators is dealt with under the loan relationships legislation. General guidance on loan relationships is at CFM30000 onwards.</p>\n\n<p>Some specific guidance on the application of thin capitalisation principles to PFI deals is given at INTM568000.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"notional-interest\">Notional interest</h2>\n\n<p>Where, as an accounting exercise, a figure representing accrued finance income on a finance debtor, i.e. notional interest, is credited to the profit and loss account (see <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/business-income-manual/bim64125\">BIM64125</a>), neither it, nor the corresponding debit to the finance debtor, is interest on a money debt for the purposes of the loan relationship legislation.</p>\n\n<p>The guidance on interest is arranged as follows:</p>\n",
